<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">Thanks for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.</font><br><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">We are writing to confirm that, as per your request,&nbsp;</font><b style="font-size: 12pt;">we have cancelled your insurance policy&nbsp;<i>(insert policy number or Add on product name)</i></b><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;with Kingsbridge&nbsp;</font><b style="font-size: 12pt;">from the date of inception&nbsp;<i>(DD MMM YYYY)</i></b><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">.</font><br><br><u style="font-size: 12pt;">It’s important to note that you are now no longer able to claim under this policy, so please disregard any previous documentation you have received from us as null and void</u><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">.</font><br><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">Since your Kingsbridge insurance policy has been cancelled,&nbsp;</font><u style="font-size: 12pt;">we want to ensure you're aware that your business may not be covered against claims if you don't have another insurance policy in place</u><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">. To help you stay protected, we recommend exploring alternative cover options. If you have any questions or need assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out to our customer service team.</font><br><br><br><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Cancelling your payment</b><br><br><font face="arial">Any payments due within 3 working days of cancellation may still be processed. We will then refund any payments taken to the account from which you originally paid within 5 to 15 working days.</font><br><br><br><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Making a claim<br></b><br><b><font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Although your previous insurance policy&nbsp;</span></font><i style="font-size: 12pt;">(active between DD MMM YYYY to DD MMM YYYY)</i><font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;with Kingsbridge expired, you may still be able to make a claim on this policy.&nbsp;</span></font></b><br><br><i style="font-size: 12pt;">(Use if for IR35)&nbsp;</i><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">IR35 Protect operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, so the policy must be active to respond to most claims. However, for&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">sections 10-12</a><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</font><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.</font><br><br><i style="font-size: 12pt;">(Use for Legal Expenses)</i><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;Legal Expenses cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. However, for&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">section 10</a><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</font><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.</font><br><br><i style="font-size: 12pt;">(Use for Cyber Liability)&nbsp;</i><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">Cyber Liability cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. For some sections of the cover however, you can notify us of a claim up to 30 days following your policy expiry date</font><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">. Please see your&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">policy wording</a><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;for full details.</font><br><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">If you are unsure whether you can make a claim on a cancelled policy, please contact our customer service team and we will be happy to help.</font><br><br><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">Whether you’re currently insured with Kingsbridge or not, our customer service team is always here to help. Please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.</font><br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br><span style="font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>